#!/usr/bin/env python3
# Author: Ximan Ding (x.ding25@imperial.ac.uk)
# Script: 14_compute_shap_results.py
# Description:
#     Prepare a fixed independent-test-set sample and compute SHAP values
#     for the trained Random Forest and XGBoost relative-abundance models.
#
#     This script:
#     1. Reads the trained Random Forest and XGBoost models;
#     2. Reads the complete test-set prediction table generated by
#        11_generate_predictions_and_metrics.py;
#     3. Rebuilds deterministic model features if required;
#     4. Excludes the pooled OTHER component from the main SHAP analysis;
#     5. Assigns reference-abundance and shallow-detection groups;
#     6. Draws a fixed random sample of test-set OTU records;
#     7. Computes row-level SHAP values for both models;
#     8. Checks whether SHAP values reconstruct the original model outputs;
#     9. Saves all outputs and analysis settings.
#
# Inputs:
#     results/models/random_forest_model.joblib
#     results/models/xgboost_model.joblib
#     results/intermediate/11_predictions_test.pkl.gz
#
# Outputs:
#     results/shap/01_shap_sample_rows.pkl.gz
#     results/shap/01_shap_sample_rows_preview.csv
#     results/shap/02_random_forest_shap_values.pkl.gz
#     results/shap/02_random_forest_shap_values_preview.csv
#     results/shap/03_xgboost_shap_values.pkl.gz
#     results/shap/03_xgboost_shap_values_preview.csv
#     results/shap/08_shap_additivity_check.csv
#     results/shap/shap_compute_config.json
#
# Arguments: None
# Date: July 2026

